he lines below were substantially further indented, there was no text below; the preserved vacat above line 1 (90mm)  is significantly greater than that between lines 1 and 2 (57mm), so it is unclear if another line originally stood above (the top of the stone appears intact) - if it did, it was either significantly above the preserved first line and/or indented several letters to the right.",{"_":35,"ana":36,"ref":37},{"ana":210},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":212,"dimensions":213},"Deep, very regular, v-cut letters, with a broad v-cut, hair-line extensions to wedge serifs, and a quite wide square module. The I in line one is extended.",[214,218,221],{"type":43,"l":215,"from":45,"to":45,"h":216,"unit":48,"atLeast":217,"atMost":217},"Line 1","68 (I = 87)","68",{"type":43,"l":219,"from":54,"to":54,"h":220,"unit":48,"atLeast":220,"atMost":220},"Line 2","58",{"type":52,"l":53,"from":45,"to":54,"h":222,"unit":48,"atLeast":222,"atMost":222},"57",{"_":224,"notBefore":156,"notAfter":59,"evidence":225},"First or second century","lettering",[227,229],{"_":62,"type":63,"ref":64,"corresp":228,"region":65},"#findspot",{"_":67,"type":68,"ref":69,"region":65},[231],[72,73],[],{"_":234,"role":78,"ref":235},"Teatro Romano di Catania","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/017",{"_":237,"mainLang":238,"languages":239},"Latin","la",[237],"644815",{"n":89,"url":242,"height":243,"width":244,"desc":245,"surfaceType":94},"ISic003420_tiled.tif","4080px","3072px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2024-03-19",[247,249,251],{"atLeast":248,"atMost":248},68,{"atLeast":250,"atMost":250},58,{"atLeast":252,"atMost":252},57,[103,254],"Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano",[108,256],"RZSFKACR",[258,259,260,15,19,261,113,114,115,116,114,262,263,238],"isic003420","fragment of an imperial honorific",{"_":12},"coarse-grained, h